>         "text": "use harness\n\n# S1 — Auth contract seam (plugin-auth-core) — P0, unblocks S2\n\nYou are a WSL Codex implementation agent under the NetScript harness (8-phase model; you implement,\nyou do NOT self-certify; a separate OpenHands session runs IMPL-EVAL). **Activate the repo skills\nbefore any task work** — this is mandatory, not optional: read\n`.agents/skills/netscript-harness/SKILL.md`, `.agents/skills/netscript-doctrine/SKILL.md` (contract\npackage archetype + public surface), and `.agents/skills/jsr-audit/SKILL.md` (JSR §5 below). If a\nskill is named but absent under `.claude/skills/`, read the `.agents/skills/<name>/SKILL.md` source.\n\n## SKILL (activate these BEFORE any task work — be generous, read each SKILL.md)\n- **`netscript-harness`** — you run under the 8-phase harness; this governs run artifacts, slice\n  commits, IMPL-EVAL separation, and the no-self-certify rule. Activate first.\n- **`netscript-doctrine`** — `plugin-auth-core` is a **contract package** archetype; doctrine governs\n  its public surface (mod.ts export rules), archetype gates, and where debt is recorded. Essential\n  for the contract-seam refactor.\n- **`jsr-audit`** — drives §5 (100% source-controllable JSR score for this package): `@module` on\n  every entrypoint, `@example` on the public surface, no-slow-types, `deno doc --lint` over the full\n  export set, `deno publish --dry-run`.\n- **`netscript-deno-toolchain`** — native Deno 2.8 toolchain for `deno doc`/`deno publish`/type\n  inspection; use `deno doc <module>` to learn a package's public surface cheaply before reading\n  source.\n- **`netscript-tools`** — scoped validation wrappers (`run-deno-{check,lint,fmt}.ts`), raw git\n  verification, lock-hygiene decisions, evidence capture.\n- **`netscript-pr`** — if/when you open or update this slice's leaf PR or post a phase comment.\n- **`codex-wsl-remote`** — your own launch/steer/push-safety mechanics (explicit-refspec push,\n  one-send-per-worktree).\n- **`rtk`** — prefix read-heavy `git`/`grep`/`ls` with `rtk` and wrap `deno task` runs in\n  `rtk proxy` to cut output tokens 60–90%.\n\n## Worktree / branch / push (READ FIRST — push-safety is mandatory)\n- Worktree: `/home/codex/repos/netscript-pt-auth-s1-contract` (already created for you).\n- Branch: `feat/prime-time/auth-s1-contract`, based on the umbrella tip `c1d957b9`\n  (`feat/prime-time/auth`). This branch has **NO upstream** by design.\n- **Push ONLY with an explicit refspec:** `git push origin HEAD:refs/heads/feat/prime-time/auth-s1-contract`.\n  NEVER run a bare `git push` and NEVER push to `feat/prime-time/auth` or `main`. (The repo's\n  `push.default=upstream` makes a bare push fail loudly — do not \"fix\" that by setting an upstream.)\n- Commit by slice; after each commit append the commit hash + message to this slice's `commits.md`.\n- Push via SSH (you are GitHub-API-blind; do not embed any token anywhere).\n\n## The single root cause you are fixing\nThe oRPC contract→handler typing seam is ERASED at the contract package. The contract is built with\nthe `oc` builder, then cast `as unknown as`/assigned onto a hand-rolled structural shim, so the real\noRPC inferred type never leaves the package. Downstream (`plugins/auth`, handled by S2) is then\nforced into `os.router(authV1 as any)` and per-handler `try/catch`. **You fix the contract side so\nS2 can adopt a real typed `$context` wrapper.**\n\n## The bar — gold-standard recipe (mirror exactly)\nContract-first `implement()` with ONE centralized cast living in the contract package:\n```ts\nexport type AuthContractV1 = Readonly<{ $context: <TContext>() => AuthRouter }>;\nexport const authContractV1: AuthContractV1 = implement(authContractDefinition) as unknown as AuthContractV1;\n```\nExemplar to mirror precisely: `plugins/sagas/contracts/v1/sagas.contract.ts:650-659` (and the\n`SagasContractV1 = Readonly<{ $context: <T>() => SagasRouter }>` type shape). The `$context` wrapper\nmust expose the REAL inferred procedures and the inferred `errors` set so S2's handlers get full\ntype inference and the central `ErrorHandlingPlugin` owns the error taxonomy.\n\n## CAST POLICY — NON-NEGOTIABLE (E2E type soundness)\nNetScript is an end-to-end fully type-safe framework. The ONLY type assertion S1 may retain is the\n**single** centralized `as unknown as AuthContractV1` shown above (recipe item 1), living once in the\ncontract package. Every other `as` / `as unknown as` / `as never` / `as any` / hand-rolled\nstructural shim in `plugin-auth-core` MUST be ELIMINATED — not narrowed, not deferred, not left as\ndebt. If removing one proves genuinely architectural (ripples beyond this package's surface), record\n`significant`/`architectural` drift in `drift.md` and STOP for a rescope decision — do NOT reintroduce\nor keep a cast to make the slice fit.\n\n## In scope (boundary = `packages/plugin-auth-core` ONLY)\nThe verified target paths (confirm exact lines on-branch; they were verified by PLAN-EVAL):\n1. **`src/contracts/v1/auth.contract.ts` (~276-313).** Replace the hand-rolled\n   `AuthContractDefinition = Readonly<{...}>` shim and the shim-typed export\n   `export const authContractV1: AuthContractDefinition = authContract;` (line ~313) with the\n   `implement(...) as unknown as AuthContractV1` typed `$context` wrapper. Delete the shim\n   interfaces `AuthContractSchema`, `AuthContractProcedureLike`, `StandardSchemaLike`,\n   `AuthContractDefinition`. Let `oc.errors` infer (do not hand-redeclare the error set).\n2. **`src/config/mod.ts`** — delete the `AuthConfigSchemaLike` hand-rolled shim; use the real\n   Zod/oRPC `StandardSchemaV1` shape.\n3. **`src/domain/mod.ts`** — delete the `AuthDomainSchema` hand-rolled shim.\n4. **`src/streams/mod.ts` (~111-115)** — remove the\n   `authStreamSchema = defineStreamSchema(...) as unknown as StateSchema<AuthStreamDefinition>` cast\n   and the `AuthStreamSchema` shim; let the schema infer.\n5. **Collapse the duplicated `AuthSession` schema.** Both `domain/mod.ts` and `streams/mod.ts`\n   define an `AuthSessionZodSchema` for the same type. Keep the `domain` copy as the single source;\n   delete the `streams` copy and import from `domain`.\n6. **Compile-time contract test (seam regression guard).** Add a type-level test under the package's\n   test surface that (a) asserts `authContractV1.$context<...>()` exposes the real inferred\n   procedures and `errors`, and (b) asserts the consolidated `AuthSession` schema identity (domain\n   vs the former streams copy resolve to the same type) — so any future drift fails `deno check`.\n\n### MUST NOT regress (public surface)\n- KEEP the named input/response types (`SigninInput`, `SigninResponse`, … `MeResponse`) and their\n  re-export path (`plugins/auth/contracts.ts:7` consumes them). You delete only the shim\n  *interfaces* and the shim-typed `const`, NOT the named DTO types.\n- Only `plugins/auth` consumes this package internally; there is no external consumer, so exporting\n  the real inferred contract type is a safe in-workspace change. Do not add a migration shim.\n\n## §5 — JSR readiness (drive `@netscript/plugin-auth-core` to 100% source-controllable JSR score)\nScope JSR work to THIS package only. Using the `jsr-audit` skill, ensure:\n- `@module` doc-comment on EVERY entrypoint in the package's `exports` map (not just `mod.ts`).\n- JSDoc on the public symbols, with at least one `@example` per primary exported surface\n  (contract, ports, domain, config, streams entrypoints).\n- **No slow types** — this aligns with the cast removal; exported signatures must be explicitly\n  typed so `deno doc --lint` and `deno publish --dry-run` emit zero slow-type warnings.\n- `description` ≤ 250 chars in the package config; runtime-compat markers present.\n- Provenance is publish-time (GitHub OIDC) — out of scope for this slice; do not attempt it.\n\n## Gates (surface-scoped — do NOT run scaffold.runtime)\nRun from the worktree root, prefer the scoped wrappers and `rtk proxy`:\n- `deno run --allow-read --allow-run .llm/tools/run-deno-check.ts --root packages/plugin-auth-core --ext ts,tsx` (include `--unstable-kv` if needed)\n- `deno run --allow-read --allow-run .llm/tools/run-deno-lint.ts --root packages/plugin-auth-core --ext ts,tsx`\n- `deno run --allow-read --allow-run .llm/tools/run-deno-fmt.ts --root packages/plugin-auth-core --ext ts,tsx`\n- Targeted package tests (incl. the new compile-time contract test).\n- **JSR gate (this package):** `deno doc --lint` over the FULL export set (every entrypoint, not\n  just `mod.ts`) → 0 issues; `rtk proxy deno publish --dry-run` (scoped to this package) → zero\n  slow-type warnings + clean file list.\n- Do NOT modify `deno.lock` (no dependency change here). Do NOT touch `@netscript/cli`.\n\n## Harness artifacts (write as you go, under this slice dir)\n`worklog.md` (gate evidence), `commits.md` (append per commit), `drift.md` (any divergence;\nmandatory if any cast can't be cleanly removed), `context-pack.md` (resumable summary). Do NOT\nself-certify — IMPL-EVAL (OpenHands qwen3.7-max, separate session) issues the verdict.\n\n## Done = ready for IMPL-EVAL\nZero casts in `plugin-auth-core` except the single centralized `as unknown as AuthContractV1`; the\ntyped `$context` wrapper exported; shims + duplicate schema gone; compile-time contract test green;\nall surface-scoped gates green; JSR doc-lint + dry-run clean; branch pushed via explicit refspec;\n`commits.md`/`worklog.md` updated.",
